Variant: duration_abs_saturation_0e99ae7_1
Fix commit: 0e99ae76a8dbbbf34a4950be6e6396cc88cc6486
Direction: fixed -> buggy (applying installs the bug).

Reverts the saturating_abs guard introduced in 0e99ae76 so that when
`self.seconds == i64::MIN` the `saturating_abs()` returns `i64::MAX` while the
nanoseconds component is left as-is (possibly negative). Base tree uses
`new_ranged_unchecked`; we restore the buggy shape using that same helper so
the patch applies on the current tree.

diff --git a/time/src/duration.rs b/time/src/duration.rs
--- a/time/src/duration.rs
+++ b/time/src/duration.rs
@@ -365,10 +365,7 @@ impl Duration {
     /// ```
     #[inline]
     pub const fn abs(self) -> Self {
-        match self.seconds.checked_abs() {
-            Some(seconds) => Self::new_ranged_unchecked(seconds, self.nanoseconds.abs()),
-            None => Self::MAX,
-        }
+        Self::new_ranged_unchecked(self.seconds.saturating_abs(), self.nanoseconds.abs())
     }

